      "body" : "@itoffshore Cool. Characters which need to be escaped in URLs break some applications, I'd recommend leaving out the symbols. The ones Bitcoin itself generates are just a base58 encoded 256-bit value. (I believe I've seen % and & both cause problems, ! is sometimes annoying if specifying the strings on the command line). Looks fine generally, the lack of error handling (e.g. /dev/urandom couldn't be opened, or something doesn't support the -c extension to head) might be concerning but bitcoin won't let you run with a too short rpcpassword.  Sorry for the diversion. :)\r\n",
